=========================================
Listener to Extent Report - Step by Step
=========================================

Step 1: Add Extent Report Dependency
------------------------------------
- Add the Extent Report dependency in pom.xml.

Step 2: Create a Listener Class
-------------------------------
- Create a class (Example: ExtentReportManager).
- Implement the ITestListener interface.

Example:
public class ExtentReportManager implements ITestListener

Why?
----
- So that TestNG automatically notifies the Listener
whenever a test starts, passes, fails, skips, or finishes.

-------------------------------------------------------

Step 3: Create the Required Objects
-----------------------------------

ExtentSparkReporter sparkReporter;
----------------------------------
- Creates the HTML report.
- Responsible for the UI/design of the report.

ExtentReports extent;
---------------------
- Main report manager.
- Attaches the reporter.
- Stores system information.
- Generates the final report.

ExtentTest test;
----------------
- Represents a single test case.
- Logs PASS, FAIL, and SKIP status.

-------------------------------------------------------

Step 4: Configure the Report (onStart())
----------------------------------------
- Create the HTML report.
- Set Report Title.
- Set Report Name.
- Set Theme.
- Add System Information.
- Attach the Spark Reporter to ExtentReports.

This method executes only once before the test execution starts.

-------------------------------------------------------

Step 5: Update Test Status
--------------------------

onTestSuccess()
---------------
- Create a test entry.
- Log PASS status.

onTestFailure()
---------------
- Create a test entry.
- Log FAIL status.
- Log the exception.
- (Generally attach a screenshot.)

onTestSkipped()
---------------
- Create a test entry.
- Log SKIP status.

-------------------------------------------------------

Step 6: Flush the Report (onFinish())
-------------------------------------
extent.flush();

Why?
----
- Writes all the execution details to the HTML report.
- If flush() is not called, the report will not be generated properly.

-------------------------------------------------------

Execution Flow
--------------

TestNG Executes Tests
        ↓
Listener Receives Events
        ↓
onStart()
        ↓
Create & Configure Report
        ↓
Test Executes
        ↓
onTestSuccess() / onTestFailure() / onTestSkipped()
        ↓
Update Extent Report
        ↓
onFinish()
        ↓
extent.flush()
        ↓
HTML Report Generated

-------------------------------------------------------

Interview Summary
-----------------
1. Create a Listener class by implementing ITestListener.
2. Create ExtentSparkReporter, ExtentReports, and ExtentTest objects.
3. Configure the report in onStart().
4. Log PASS, FAIL, and SKIP results in the respective Listener methods.
5. Call extent.flush() in onFinish() to generate the final HTML report.